                                <rect key="frame" x="32" y="142" width="311" height="98"/>
                                <autoresizingMask key="autoresizingMask" flexibleMaxX="YES" flexibleMaxY="YES"/>
                                <string key="text">This guessing game was made by Bryan Akin and Briana Flores as the final project in CSCI-C323 during the spring semester of 2025. </string>
                                <fontDescription key="fontDescription" type="system" pointSize="17"/>
                                <nil key="textColor"/>
                                <nil key="highlightedColor"/>
                            </label>
                            <label opaque="NO" userInteractionEnabled="NO" contentMode="left" horizontalHuggingPriority="251" verticalHuggingPriority="251" fixedFrame="YES" textAlignment="natural" lineBreakMode="tailTruncation" numberOfLines="15" baselineAdjustment="alignBaselines" adjustsFontSizeToFit="NO" translatesAutoresizingMaskIntoConstraints="NO" id="M9M-il-SiN">
                                <rect key="frame" x="32" y="294" width="304" height="268"/>
                                <autoresizingMask key="autoresizingMask" flexibleMaxX="YES" flexibleMaxY="YES"/>
                                <string key="text">The game contains 3 difficulty levels which adjust the size of the board. You have 10 seconds to memorize what the board looks like then you try to recreate it. You can either choose a difficulty or have a random one set for you. The remember order mode shows the board as its being set and you have to try and set it in the same order. When your game is finished, you can either play again with the same rules or drag down from near the tp of the screen to go back to the start page. </string>
                                <fontDescription key="fontDescription" type="system" pointSize="17"/>
                                <nil key="textColor"/>
                                <nil key="highlightedColor"/>
                            </label>
